Dia. 05 Following the Fundamentals
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black has to fill the liberties from the outside again. Black 1 and 3 can be exchanged.
\par
\par It is same with the previous problem, isn't it?
\par
\par In a capturing race, except when a special maek is needed, playing on the outside liberties is a \cf1\b fundamental rule for winning the capturing race\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par }
